The paper deals with communication complexity in combinatorial auctions, which is a topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.DS). The use of subadditive functions and the MPH hierarchy suggests a connection to approximation algorithms and optimization (cs.AI), while the discussion of strategic bidders indicates a connection to mechanism design and economic theory (cs.EC). Finally, the use of communication complexity as a measure of hardness suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT).
